The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered a speech at the White House to celebrate the 69th anniversary of Israel's independence. He expressed America's unwavering support for Israel and its people, highlighting President Donald Trump's commitment to the nation. Pence emphasized the historical ties between Israel and the United States, as well as the shared values and fight against common enemies. He also mentioned the progress being made towards resolving the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, while ensuring the safety and security of Israel. Pence praised Israel's strength and resilience, and vowed that America would continue to stand strong against terrorism and the leading state sponsor of terrorism, Iran. He concluded his speech by expressing confidence in the future of Israel and America, and called for God's blessings on both nations.